snippet.title: Is Low Cadence More Naturally Efficient For Cyclists? (Ask a Cycling Coach 285)
snippet.description:
Is there such a thing as an optimal cadence?  Learn if lower cadence is more efficient, does greater efficiency yield better performance and more in this Quick Clip from Episode 285 of The Ask a Cycling Coach Podcast. 

• Watch more of this Ask a Cycling Coach Episode: https://youtu.be/-pimf70RBDU 

• Find links to mentioned studies and join the discussion on the TrainerRoad Forum: https://bit.ly/3lYYq0d
